:: Submit [nobr]
/*
SAVING SPINNER. Fires CCQ.submitResponse to land the answers in
`surveys/control_daily_checkin/responses/{auto}` via SurveyHooks. The
700ms delay is cosmetic — OfflineQueue writes are fire-and-forget so
the bridge call returns immediately, but giving the participant a
moment to register that something happened feels less abrupt.
*/
<div class="phone center-text">
  <div class="header"><span>Daily Check-In</span></div>
  <h1>Saving your answers</h1>
  <p class="lead">Just a moment…</p>
  <div class="spinner" aria-label="Saving"></div>
</div>

<<run
  try {
    if (window.CCQ && window.CCQ.submitResponse) {
      CCQ.submitResponse(State.variables.answers, {
        surveyId: "control_daily_checkin",
        pointsEarned: 10
      });
    }
  } catch (e) { /* swallow */ }
>>

<<timed 700ms>>
  <<goto "Done">>
<</timed>>


:: Done [nobr]
<div class="phone center-text">
  <div class="header"><span>Daily Check-In</span></div>
  <h1>Thank you</h1>
  <p class="lead">
    Your answers help us learn more about how the program is working
    for people like you.
  </p>
  <div class="primary-cta">
    <<button "Back home">>
      <<goto "Central Hub">>
    <</button>>
  </div>
</div>


:: Central Hub
/*
EXIT HATCH. Fires CCQ.goHome() so the Flutter host pops the WebView's
route back to the dashboard. No UI on purpose — the host pops before
the player sees anything; in twinery.org preview the bridge no-ops
and the loading text is the visible result.
*/
<<run if (window.CCQ && typeof window.CCQ.goHome === "function") { window.CCQ.goHome(); }>>

<div class="phone center-text">
  <div class="header"><span>Daily Check-In</span></div>
  <h1>Returning…</h1>
  <p class="lead">Heading back to the dashboard.</p>
</div>
